<ns699:section xmlns:ns699="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.concepts.architecture.referenceArchitectures.j2ee.whatIsJavaEe">
  <ns700:title xmlns:ns700="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">What is Java EE</ns700:title>
   <ns701:para xmlns:ns701="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
     Java EE is a multi-tier reference architecture which addresses  many of the quality
     requirements of typical enterprise systems including
     <ns702:itemizedlist xmlns:ns702="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
       <ns703:listitem xmlns:ns703="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns704:para xmlns:ns704="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         <ns705:emphasis xmlns:ns705="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">scalablity</ns705:emphasis> through resource pooling (including object, thread
         and connection pooling) and clustering,
       </ns704:para></ns703:listitem>
       <ns706:listitem xmlns:ns706="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns707:para xmlns:ns707="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         <ns708:emphasis xmlns:ns708="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">reliability</ns708:emphasis> through transactional support and clustering,
       </ns707:para></ns706:listitem>
       <ns709:listitem xmlns:ns709="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns710:para xmlns:ns710="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         <ns711:emphasis xmlns:ns711="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">maintainability</ns711:emphasis> through separation of business logic from
         presentation logic, persistence logic and infrastructure logic, and by enforcing
         contracts based decoupling through local and remote interfaces,
       </ns710:para></ns709:listitem>
       <ns712:listitem xmlns:ns712="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns713:para xmlns:ns713="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         <ns714:emphasis xmlns:ns714="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">security</ns714:emphasis> through standardification of authentication, support
         for secure communication and message integrity and role based authorization,
       </ns713:para></ns712:listitem>
       <ns715:listitem xmlns:ns715="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns716:para xmlns:ns716="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         <ns717:emphasis xmlns:ns717="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">integrability</ns717:emphasis> through support for integration standards like
         web services, CORBA and messaging, by providing a standard connector infrastructure (JCA) 
         for proprietary and custom integration technologies and by providing solid object oriented
         XML to Java mapping (JAXB).
       </ns716:para></ns715:listitem>
       <ns718:listitem xmlns:ns718="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns719:para xmlns:ns719="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
         <ns720:emphasis xmlns:ns720="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">portability</ns720:emphasis> across both, vendors and platforms by specifying
         a set of standard APIs for the Java EE components and by being Java based.
       </ns719:para></ns718:listitem>
     </ns702:itemizedlist>
     
   </ns701:para>
</ns699:section>